```

Since pretty much all the `metadata` setting reducers are exactly the same, it's really tempting to make a `SET_IN_CELL_METADATA` action/reducer pair, where the utility functions like `updateCellTags` only returns the metadata data change update:

```js
export function updateCellTags(id: CellID, tags: any) {
  return {
    type: constants.SET_IN_CELL_METADATA,
    id,
    path: ["metadata", "tags"],
    value: tags
  }
}
```

Maybe this could just be:
